  "prompt": "Bank Accounts: How do I know whether my bank account is linked to my Aadhaar card or not?",
  "response": "To check if your bank account is linked to your Aadhaar card, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Online methods:\n- Check your bank's net banking portal\n- Log into your bank's mobile banking app\n- Visit the UIDAI website (uidai.gov.in)\n\n2. Offline methods:\n- Visit your bank branch\n- Call your bank's customer care\n- Check your passbook or bank statement\n\n3. SMS method:\n- Send an SMS to your bank's designated number\n- Format may vary by bank\n\n4. Through Aadhaar website:\n- Go to uidai.gov.in\n- Click on \"Aadhaar Seeding Status\"\n- Enter your bank account number\n- Provide other required details\n\n5. Verification through missed call:\n- Some banks provide a missed call number to check Aadhaar linking status\n\n6. Documents to verify:\n- Bank passbook\n- Account statement\n- Online banking profile\n\nPro Tips:\n- Keep your Aadhaar number and bank account details handy\n- Contact bank customer service for specific guidance\n- Linking is mandatory for receiving government benefits\n\nRemember, procedures might slightly differ depending on your bank.",
